$ SAS programming - macro function: %str
@ %str

`%str` should be used
  • to treat semicolons (`;`) as text rather than as macro statement delimiter,
  • to maintain blanks within values
  • when quoation marks or parantheses are not balanced.

gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/functions/str.sas||

→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/functions/nrstr[`%nrstr`] is like `%str` except that is also masks `%` and `&`.

